{"id":978926809,"question_id":2831,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"11 months, 3 weeks","timestamp":1687661263,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"157 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/978926809/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Number of Beautiful Pairs","memory":"44.7 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public int countBeautifulPairs(int[] nums) {\n        \n        HashSet<String> set = new HashSet<>();\n        \n        int len = nums.length;\n        int cnt =0;\n        for(int i=0; i<len; i++){\n            for(int j=i+1; j<len; j++){\n                \n                int x = firstDigit(nums[i]);\n                int y = lastDigit(nums[j]);\n                \n                \n                if(gcd(x, y)==1){\n                    cnt++;\n                    if(x>=y)\n                    \n                        set.add(x+\"_\"+y);\n\n                    else \n                        set.add(y+\"_\"+x);\n                    \n                    \n                    // System.out.println(x+ \" \" + y);\n                }\n                    \n            }\n            \n            \n        }\n        \n        return cnt;\n    }\n    \n    \n    \n    private int gcd(int a, int b){\n        \n        if(b==0) return a;\n        return gcd(b, a%b);\n        \n    }\n    \n    private int firstDigit(int x){\n        \n        String s = String.valueOf(x);\n        return s.charAt(0)-'0';\n        \n    }\n    \n    private int lastDigit(int x){\n        \n        String s = String.valueOf(x);\n        return s.charAt(s.length()-1)-'0';\n        \n    }\n        \n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"number-of-beautiful-pairs","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
